race.comment: CONFEDERATE LADY (3) was far from disgraced to finish 1.5L adrift over 1015m at Grafton when she made plenty of late ground. That followed a first-up win at Port Macquarie, where she was also well-supported. Has a solid record at this course and finally draws a low barrier. MONACO FLYER (4) returned from a break last start with an all-the-way win over 1015m at Grafton. He's further improved and fitter is sure to take some stopping again. AMAYA'S SECRET (2) resumed over 1015m at Grafton and raced handy until the fitness gave out late. She is proven second up and has plenty up her sleeve. Winning claims on her best figures. BACK ON DE QUO (5) was in a different class with a dominant all-the-way win at this track over 1000m first up. This is a step-up, but he has weight relief and is sure to give a sight.
